<def f='linux-4.18.y/include/linux/i2c.h' l='123' ll='128' type='int i2c_master_send_dmasafe(const struct i2c_client * client, const char * buf, int count)'/>
<doc f='linux-4.18.y/include/linux/i2c.h' l='114'>/**
 * i2c_master_send_dmasafe - issue a single I2C message in master transmit mode
 *			     using a DMA safe buffer
 * @client: Handle to slave device
 * @buf: Data that will be written to the slave, must be safe to use with DMA
 * @count: How many bytes to write, must be less than 64k since msg.len is u16
 *
 * Returns negative errno, or else the number of bytes written.
 */</doc>
